<div class="views-field views-field-title"> <span class=field-content><a href="events/secure-15-2-factor-authentication-webinar">Secure 1.5 &amp; 2 factor authentication Webinar</a></span> </div>
<div class="views-field views-field-field-date-and-time"> <span class=field-content><span class=date-display-single property=dc:date datatype=xsd:dateTime content="2013-03-01T10:30:00+00:00">01-Mar-2013</span></span> </div>
<div class="views-field views-field-body"> <div class=field-content><p><span style="color:#333;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5em">Find out more about how using a PINgrid you can provide a strong, simple to use logon system.</span></p>
<p style="font-size:12px;line-height:1.5em;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1.5em;color:#333;font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif">PINgrid takes advantage of the mind's ability to remember patterns and shapes. Users don't need to carry additional items like key fobs or tokens, nor do they need to remember more passwords or PINS.</p></div> </div>
